import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
from sklearn.gaussian_process import GaussianProcessRegressor
from sklearn.gaussian_process.kernels import RBF
from PIL import Image
import glob
In [2]:
# RBF(length_scale)
gpr = GaussianProcessRegressor(RBF(length_scale=0.2))

# 
n = 1000

# X_ = [0, 10]n
X_ = np.linspace(0, 10, n)

# X_shape(n, )(n, 1)
# predictshape =n_samplesn_features
#  : https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.gaussian_process.GaussianProcessRegressor.html
X_ = X_.reshape(n, 1)

# predict(fity_mean=0, y_std=1)
y_mean, y_std = gpr.predict(X_, return_std=True)

# 
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16, 10))

# 
plt.xlim(min(X_) , max(X_))
plt.ylim(-5, 5)

# y_mean
plt.plot(X_, y_mean, color="black", linewidth=5)

# y_std[mean-std, mean+std](1alpha)
# X_shape(n, 1)(n, )
# fill_betweenarray (length N))
#  : https://matplotlib.org/api/_as_gen/matplotlib.pyplot.fill_between.html
plt.fill_between(X_.reshape(n,), y_mean - y_std, y_mean + y_std, alpha=0.3, color="black")

# gpr(10)
# fit
# X_shape(n, )(n, 1)
# sample_yshape =n_samplesn_features
#  : https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.gaussian_process.GaussianProcessRegressor.html
y_samples = gpr.sample_y(X_.reshape(n, 1), 10)
plt.plot(X_, y_samples, lw=1)

# on
plt.title("Ovserved data:0, Gray:1", fontsize=30)
plt.xlabel("X", fontsize=20)
plt.ylabel("Y", fontsize=20)
plt.grid(True)


# gif0.png
plt.savefig("./0.png")

plt.show()

# [0, 10]5
# y = sin(x)
# gprfit(reshape)
# mean, std

observed = 5
X_train = np.random.RandomState(1).uniform(0, 10, observed)
y_train = np.sin(X_train)
gpr.fit(X_train.reshape(observed, 1), y_train)

# predict(fity_mean=0, y_std=1)
y_mean, y_std = gpr.predict(X_.reshape(n, 1), return_std=True)

# 
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16, 10))

# 
plt.xlim(min(X_) , max(X_))
plt.ylim(-5, 5)

# 
plt.scatter(X_train.reshape(observed, ), 
            y_train, 
            s=100,
            color="red",
            marker="o")

# y_mean
plt.plot(X_, y_mean, color="black", linewidth=5)

# y_std[mean-std, mean+std](1alpha)
# X_shape(n, 1)(n, )
# fill_betweenarray (length N))
#  : https://matplotlib.org/api/_as_gen/matplotlib.pyplot.fill_between.html
plt.fill_between(X_.reshape(n,), 
                 y_mean - y_std, 
                 y_mean + y_std, 
                 alpha=0.3, 
                 color="black")

# gpr(10)
# fit
# X_shape(n, )(n, 1)
# sample_yshape =n_samplesn_features
#  : https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.gaussian_process.GaussianProcessRegressor.html
y_samples = gpr.sample_y(X_.reshape(n, 1), 10)
plt.plot(X_, y_samples, lw=1)

# 
plt.title("Observed data:{}, Gray:1".format(observed), fontsize=30)
plt.xlabel("X", fontsize=20)
plt.ylabel("Y", fontsize=20)
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

In [5]:
for i in range(1,10):

    observed = i
    X_train = np.random.RandomState(1).uniform(0, 10, observed)
    y_train = np.sin(X_train)
    gpr.fit(X_train.reshape(observed, 1), y_train)

    # predict(fity_mean=0, y_std=1)
    y_mean, y_std = gpr.predict(X_.reshape(n, 1), return_std=True)

    # 
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16, 10))

    # 
    plt.xlim(min(X_) , max(X_))
    plt.ylim(-5, 5)

    # 
    plt.scatter(X_train.reshape(observed, ), 
                y_train, 
                s=100,
                color="red",
                marker="o")

    # y_mean
    plt.plot(X_, y_mean, color="black", linewidth=5)

    # y_std[mean-std, mean+std](1alpha)
    # X_shape(n, 1)(n, )
    # fill_betweenarray (length N))
    #  : https://matplotlib.org/api/_as_gen/matplotlib.pyplot.fill_between.html
    plt.fill_between(X_.reshape(n,), 
                     y_mean - y_std, 
                     y_mean + y_std, 
                     alpha=0.3, 
                     color="black")

    # gpr(10)
    # fit
    # X_shape(n, )(n, 1)
    # sample_yshape =n_samplesn_features
    #  : https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.gaussian_process.GaussianProcessRegressor.html
    y_samples = gpr.sample_y(X_.reshape(n, 1), 10)
    plt.plot(X_, y_samples, lw=1)

    # (.png)
    plt.title("Observed data:{}, Gray:1".format(observed), fontsize=30)
    plt.xlabel("X", fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel("Y", fontsize=20)
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.savefig("{}.png".format(i))
